  "abstract": {
    "value": "A methodology for the formal addition of β-acylalkenyl anions was developed by utilizing the [1,2]-phospha-Brook rearrangement under Brønsted base catalysis. The two-step reaction involves the catalytic addition of α-oxygenated propargyl anions generated via [1,2]-phospha-Brook rearrangement to electron-deficient ketones and subsequent alcoholysis to afford tertiary alcohols having an enone moiety. This is a rare example of a catalytic carbon-carbon bond forming reaction of β-acylalkenyl anion equivalents, providing synthetic building blocks that are otherwise difficult to access.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
    "confidence": 0.98,
    "human_checked": false
  },
